recalls.Summary: McLaren Automotive Incorporated (McLaren) is recalling certain 2012-2013 MP4-12C, 2014-2016 650s, 2015-2016 675 LT, 2014-2015 P1 and 2015-2017 570 vehicles.  These vehicles are equipped with air bag inflators assembled as part of the passenger frontal air bag modules, used as original equipment or replacement equipment (such as after a vehicle crash necessitating replacement of the original air bags), that may explode due to propellant degradation occurring after long-term exposure to high absolute humidity, temperature and temperature cycling.
recalls.Consequence: An inflator explosion may result in sharp metal fragments striking the driver or other occupants resulting in serious injury or death.
recalls.Remedy: McLaren will notify owners, and dealers will replace the air bags, free of charge.  The recall began March 28, 2019.  Owners may contact McLaren customer service at 1-646-429-8916.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

issues.title: Door Handle Mechanism Failure
issues.description: The electronic door handles on the 650S are prone to failure, particularly the mechanism that retracts and extends the handle. This can result in doors being difficult or impossible to open from the outside.
symptoms: Door handle doesn't extend when approached
Handle gets stuck in retracted position
issues.fix_description: Replace the door handle mechanism and related electronic components
issues.prevention: Avoid forcing handles and keep door sensors clean

issues.title: Hydraulic Suspension System Leaks
issues.description: The active suspension system can develop leaks in hydraulic lines and actuators, causing the car to sit unevenly or lose ride height adjustment capability.
symptoms: Car sits lower on one corner
issues.fix_description: Replace faulty hydraulic actuators, lines, or pump components
issues.prevention: Regular suspension system inspections and avoiding harsh impacts

issues.title: Carbon Fiber Body Panel Delamination
issues.description: Carbon fiber body panels, particularly around high-stress areas like door frames and rear spoiler mounts, can experience delamination or cracking over time.
issues.fix_description: Professional carbon fiber repair or panel replacement
issues.prevention: Avoid impacts and extreme temperature changes

issues.title: Infotainment System Freezing
issues.description: The IRIS infotainment system is prone to freezing, slow response times, and occasional complete system crashes requiring a restart.
issues.fix_description: Software updates or infotainment unit replacement
issues.prevention: Regular software updates and avoiding extreme temperatures

issues.title: Engine Oil Consumption Issues
issues.description: The 3.8L twin-turbo V8 engine can exhibit higher than normal oil consumption, particularly in track-driven vehicles or those with higher mileage.
issues.fix_description: Engine inspection, possible ring or valve seal replacement
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes with high-quality oil and avoiding extended high-RPM operation

issues.title: Brake System Overheating
issues.description: During aggressive driving or track use, the brake system can overheat, leading to brake fade and potential safety concerns.
issues.fix_description: Upgrade brake pads, rotors, and brake fluid to track-spec components
issues.prevention: Use appropriate brake cooling and high-performance brake components for track use

issues.title: Electrical System Glitches
issues.description: Various electrical issues including dashboard warning lights, sensor malfunctions, and intermittent electronic component failures.
issues.fix_description: Diagnose specific electrical faults and replace faulty components or wiring
issues.prevention: Regular electrical system checks and avoiding aftermarket modifications

issues.title: Turbocharger Wastegate Issues
issues.description: The turbocharger wastegate actuators can fail or stick, leading to overboosting or underperformance of the engine.
issues.fix_description: Replace wastegate actuators or complete turbocharger units
issues.prevention: Regular turbo system maintenance and quality fuel usage

issues.title: Clutch Wear in Automatic Transmission
issues.description: The dual-clutch automatic transmission can experience premature clutch wear, especially in stop-and-go traffic or aggressive driving conditions.
issues.fix_description: Clutch pack replacement and transmission service
issues.prevention: Proper driving techniques and regular transmission maintenance

issues.title: Paint Quality Issues
issues.description: Some 650S models have experienced paint quality issues including orange peel texture, color matching problems, and premature paint deterioration.
issues.fix_description: Professional paint correction or repainting of affected panels
issues.prevention: Regular paint protection and avoiding harsh environmental conditions

editorial.hero_blurb: The 650S represents McLaren's formula at its most refined, delivering 641 horsepower through a chassis that balances track-ready aggression with surprising daily usability. This is supercar performance without the traditional compromises.
editorial.essence: The 650S bridges the gap between McLaren's entry-level offerings and their hypercar elite, delivering 90% of P1 performance at a fraction of the price. It's McLaren's engineering prowess distilled into its purest, most accessible form.
editorial.heritage: Born from McLaren's MP4-12C foundation but extensively revised following P1 development, the 650S incorporated aerodynamic lessons from Formula 1 and endurance racing. It served as McLaren's volume supercar, establishing the brand's reputation for everyday exotic performance.
editorial.design_philosophy: McLaren prioritized functional aerodynamics over pure aesthetics, creating aggressive bodywork that channels airflow with surgical precision. Every surface serves a purpose, from the distinctive front splitter to the integrated rear wing.
editorial.motorsport_history: While not a direct racing derivative, the 650S incorporates technologies developed through McLaren's Formula 1 program and GT racing efforts. The 650S GT3 proved highly competitive in international motorsport.
editorial.engine_character: The 3.8L twin-turbo V8 delivers power with relentless linearity, building boost progressively before unleashing a savage surge past 3,000 RPM. It's clinical in its efficiency yet emotional in its delivery.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 7-speed dual-clutch shifts with rifle-bolt precision in track mode, while comfort settings provide smooth, seamless transitions. Paddle responses are immediate and satisfying.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: The adaptive suspension transforms character on demand, from compliant grand tourer to track weapon. Body control remains exemplary even when comfort is prioritized, with minimal dive or squat under acceleration.
editorial.steering_feel: Hydraulic power steering provides genuine feedback through the carbon fiber wheel, loading up naturally in corners while remaining light enough for parking. The connection to the front wheels feels direct and honest.
editorial.brake_confidence: Carbon ceramic brakes offer tremendous stopping power with excellent pedal feel and fade resistance. Initial bite is strong but progressive, inspiring confidence on track and street alike.
editorial.sound_signature: The exhaust produces a sophisticated growl at idle, building to an angry roar under acceleration. The twin turbos add a distinctive whistle that punctuates the V8's natural soundtrack.
editorial.ideal_owner: Driving purists who want supercar performance with everyday usability, track day enthusiasts seeking reliability, and collectors who appreciate McLaren's engineering excellence without hypercar pricing.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Buyers seeking maximum comfort, those who prioritize brand prestige over driving dynamics, or owners who require extensive cargo space and rear passenger accommodation.
editorial.buyers_summary: The 650S offers exceptional value in the supercar realm, delivering genuine hypercar performance with surprising reliability. Focus on maintenance records and avoid early production examples with potential electrical gremlins.
cons: Complex electronics prone to minor issues
